	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.98]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Also, the Damage Bonus is not &quot;extra&quot; damage... it's the base damage that you will hit with... so a damage bonus of 15 means that they will never hit for less then 15 base damage... this becomes extremely important to a dual weilding class, as lower delay becomes more damage efficient with increasing damage bonus for higher levels.<br><br>Most melee classes will not get a bonus to higher delay weapons until the delay of the weapon is greater than 40... (pally/sk get bonus to 2H though)... so a 15 30 weapon would have the same dmg bonus as a 9 18... the difference? you'd be hitting for at LEAST the base damage bonus much more with the lower delay weapon.<br><br>of course, when high level haste, damage bonus, disciplines, ratios, spell effects, buffs/debuffs are taken into account... it really becomes an impossible task to determine the value of a weapon and it's damage efficiency...<br>&nbsp;<br>Darknyss Grimscale<br>52 Iksar ShadowKnight<br>21 Ranger, 20 Monk, 20 Enchanter</td></tr>
